00:28:49.270 --> 00:28:50.896
So either we can do business.

511
00:28:51.063 --> 00:28:52.523
or you can fuckin' bounce.

512
00:28:53.107 --> 00:28:54.650
-Wrong fuckin' answer.

513
00:29:18.507 --> 00:29:20.468
Look at you.
bitch-made motherfucker.

514
00:29:22.261 --> 00:29:24.138
Fuck you. you bitch-ass nigga!

515
00:29:24.305 --> 00:29:26.265
Fuck you! Fuck you!

516
00:29:26.432 --> 00:29:27.850
Fuck you!

517
00:29:27.975 --> 00:29:29.351
For fuckin' Wheelie. bitch!

518
00:29:29.518 --> 00:29:30.936
Come on. he's dead. bro.

519
00:29:33.939 --> 00:29:35.524
Fuckin' cocksuckers!

520
00:29:36.108 --> 00:29:38.152
You shoulda just served
the motherfucker up.

521
00:29:39.236 --> 00:29:41.113
You woulda made so much money.

522
00:29:44.575 --> 00:29:45.743
Goddamn. D.

523
00:29:45.910 --> 00:29:47.620
You said we need
to let motherfuckers know

524
00:29:47.786 --> 00:29:50.122
that it ain't open season
on CBI.

525
00:29:50.289 --> 00:29:52.166
Now tell the guys
they need to hang

526
00:29:52.333 --> 00:29:53.501
these motherfuckers
out to dry.

527
00:29:53.667 --> 00:29:55.544
Make the feds think
it's some cartel shit.

528
00:29:56.253 --> 00:29:59.048
And put the word out that CBI's
taking over Yardies' territory.

529
00:29:59.215 --> 00:30:00.341
Hell yeah. nigga.

530
00:30:00.508 --> 00:30:01.717
I'm gon' give a call to Che.

531
00:30:01.884 --> 00:30:04.386
Make sure we set up a meet.
He need to know about this.

532
00:30:04.553 --> 00:30:06.096
Hey. I can roll wit' you
to that though. right?

533
00:30:06.222 --> 00:30:08.015
Come on. bro. I helped
with the King Kilo shit. D-Mac--

534
00:30:08.182 --> 00:30:10.559
Relax. bro. You ain't gotta
convince me. You in.

535
00:30:41.757 --> 00:30:44.885
Ooh. yeah. Look at that.
I like what you did there.

536
00:30:45.761 --> 00:30:46.804
Do I know you?

537
00:30:46.971 --> 00:30:48.430
We met once.

538
00:30:50.432 --> 00:30:51.600
I'll give you a hint.

539
00:30:52.142 --> 00:30:53.477
The art studio...

540
00:30:53.644 --> 00:30:55.229
wasn't too different than this.

541
00:30:55.854 --> 00:30:57.398
Was it an opening?

542
00:30:59.024 --> 00:31:00.401
More like a closing.

543
00:31:03.654 --> 00:31:04.613
Oh my God.

544
00:31:04.738 --> 00:31:05.739
You were there when Colin--

545
00:31:05.906 --> 00:31:07.741
Colin closed shop. yeah.

546
00:31:07.866 --> 00:31:09.493
Oh my God. What the fuck?

547
00:31:09.618 --> 00:31:10.536
Hey. Alicia.

548
00:31:11.161 --> 00:31:11.954
Calm down.

549
00:31:12.830 --> 00:31:15.708
What are you gonna do.
shoot me in front of everybody?

550
00:31:15.833 --> 00:31:17.376
I don't want to.

551
00:31:19.044 --> 00:31:20.254
In fact...

552
00:31:21.714 --> 00:31:25.509
I'm here to offer you $25.000.

553
00:31:28.095 --> 00:31:29.430
Cash.

554
00:31:34.435 --> 00:31:35.853
But you gotta keep
your mouth shut.

555
00:31:36.020 --> 00:31:37.021
and you gotta help me.

556
00:31:37.187 --> 00:31:38.647
With what?

557
00:31:39.940 --> 00:31:41.817
You cooperated with the feds.

558
00:31:42.693 --> 00:31:44.612
And you told 'em that
Vic Flynn was the one--

559
00:31:44.778 --> 00:31:46.113
I didn't have a choice.

560
00:31:46.280 --> 00:31:49.825
Hey. what'd I just tell you?
Calm down. It's all good.

561
00:31:49.950 --> 00:31:52.786
Keep paintin'. Smile.
There you go.

562
00:31:52.953 --> 00:31:55.289
There was a prosecutor there.
You remember her?

563
00:31:55.998 --> 00:31:57.374
What about her?

564
00:31:58.417 --> 00:32:00.002
You're gonna tell me about her.

565
00:32:02.796 --> 00:32:04.006
And me and you...

566
00:32:04.882 --> 00:32:06.550
we gonna make a little video.

567
00:32:07.968 --> 00:32:09.678
And if you keep your mouth shut.

568
00:32:09.803 --> 00:32:12.222
you're gonna be $25.000 richer

569
00:32:12.806 --> 00:32:14.642
and everything gon' be fine.

570
00:32:20.648 --> 00:32:22.816
You're sending me
"meet me now" texts?

571
00:32:22.983 --> 00:32:25.194
You work for me. Remember?

572
00:32:25.361 --> 00:32:26.862
I'm here to help your campaign.

573
00:32:29.573 --> 00:32:31.575
What the fuck do you know
about my campaign? Hm?

574
00:32:31.742 --> 00:32:33.577
I know you're hurting for cash.

575
00:32:33.702 --> 00:32:35.954
Maybe Pagent Inc.
could make another donation.

576
00:32:36.121 --> 00:32:37.456
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
what the fuck is this?

577
00:32:37.623 --> 00:32:40.334
I think the better question is.
who the fuck is this?

578
00:32:40.876 --> 00:32:42.211
I'm Pagent Inc.

579
00:32:43.796 --> 00:32:46.507
Now see. that's no way
to treat your biggest donor.

580
00:32:47.132 --> 00:32:48.717
Usually it's more like.

581
00:32:48.884 --> 00:32:50.177
"Oh. shit! Nice to meet you."

582
00:32:50.344 --> 00:32:52.221
"What could I do for you
after I'm elected?"

583
00:32:52.930 --> 00:32:55.474
You don't really think that
money buys you anything. do you?

584
00:32:55.974 --> 00:32:57.393
I don't know. Stac.

585
00:32:57.559 --> 00:32:58.686
How do you think it's gonna look

586
00:32:58.852 --> 00:33:00.396
when it comes out
that you took money

587
00:33:00.562 --> 00:33:01.689
from the same drug dealer

588
00:33:01.855 --> 00:33:03.732
you've been trying
to build a case against?

589
00:33:04.233 --> 00:33:05.693
You been playing me?

590
00:33:06.110 --> 00:33:07.069
With him?

591
00:33:07.778 --> 00:33:09.029
How fucking long?

592
00:33:09.196 --> 00:33:10.406
It don't matter.

593
00:33:10.531 --> 00:33:11.490
You're an idiot.

594
00:33:11.657 --> 00:33:12.908
He's gonna chew you up.

595
00:33:13.033 --> 00:33:14.368
spit you out.

596
00:33:15.536 --> 00:33:17.413
then put a fucking bullet
in your head.

597
00:33:17.996 --> 00:33:19.832
There's no way
this ends well for you.

598
00:33:19.957 --> 00:33:22.334
And look. I didn't know
that the money came from you.

599
00:33:22.501 --> 00:33:23.335
I'll just return it.

600
00:33:23.460 --> 00:33:24.336
Or...

601
00:33:24.461 --> 00:33:25.421
you could try to get over

602
00:33:25.587 --> 00:33:26.714
this terrible. horrible.

603
00:33:26.880 --> 00:33:29.341
no-good. shitty day
you've been having.

604
00:33:29.508 --> 00:33:33.846
Seems to me the best way to get
over losing CPD's support is...

605
00:33:36.849 --> 00:33:38.350
-more money.

606
00:33:40.936 --> 00:33:45.858
So... so you think that I'm
desperate enough to become mayor

607
00:33:46.024 --> 00:33:47.443
that I'm willing to give up

608
00:33:47.609 --> 00:33:49.987
everything that I stand for.
everything that I've built.

609
00:33:50.154 --> 00:33:52.990
to jump in your pocket
for a little bit of cash?

610
00:33:54.867 --> 00:33:56.577
Think again. motherfucker.

611
00:33:56.702 --> 00:33:58.787
Nah. I don't think
you'll do it for cash.

612
00:33:58.954 --> 00:34:00.914
But I do think you'll do it
because of this.

613
00:34:01.081 --> 00:34:03.959
I met with a federal
prosecutor. Stacy Marks.

614
00:34:04.918 --> 00:34:06.879
She wanted me to ID someone
named Vic Flynn

615
00:34:07.045 --> 00:34:08.630
as the guy
who shot Colin Judge.

616
00:34:09.130 --> 00:34:10.799
And first she threatened me.

617
00:34:10.966 --> 00:34:14.844
and when I wouldn't go along.
she offered me $25.000.

618
00:34:15.344 --> 00:34:16.138
Cash.

619
00:34:16.304 --> 00:34:18.098
And I'm a starving art student.

620
00:34:18.264 --> 00:34:19.975
so... I took it.

621
00:34:20.809 --> 00:34:22.143
That's a fucking lie.

622
00:34:22.311 --> 00:34:25.105
You tampered
with a federal witness.

623
00:34:25.813 --> 00:34:27.524
I can put the fucking cuffs
on you right now.

624
00:34:27.690 --> 00:34:30.277
You could do that. but then
this will explode in the media.

625
00:34:30.444 --> 00:34:31.527
So what?

626
00:34:32.446 --> 00:34:33.906
Who do you think
they're gonna believe?

627
00:34:34.614 --> 00:34:35.824
Me...

628
00:34:36.867 --> 00:34:38.452
-or a drug dealer?
-You right.

629
00:34:38.619 --> 00:34:39.995
You could definitely
say that she's lying.

630
00:34:40.120 --> 00:34:42.498
or that I'm trying
to extort you

631
00:34:42.664 --> 00:34:44.458
by donating to your campaign.

632
00:34:44.625 --> 00:34:46.585
but... fuck me. Stacy.

633
00:34:47.503 --> 00:34:50.172
This whole thing sound like
a fucking shitshow.

634
00:34:50.297 --> 00:34:52.591
You runnin' as
the squeaky-clean candidate.

635
00:34:53.342 --> 00:34:55.511
Yet here you are.
all kind of messy.

636
00:34:55.677 --> 00:34:57.554
-What you think. Vic?
- I think DOJ

637
00:34:57.721 --> 00:34:59.640
probably opens
an ethics investigation.

638
00:34:59.765 --> 00:35:01.141
-Right? Yeah.
-Mm-hm.

639
00:35:01.308 --> 00:35:03.060
I mean. you might could
get another job.

640
00:35:03.185 --> 00:35:06.355
but it's hard to scrape
that smell of shit off you

641
00:35:06.522 --> 00:35:08.023
when you fall in the sewer.

642
00:35:09.024 --> 00:35:11.527
I can almost hear them gears
grindin' up there.

643
00:35:11.693 --> 00:35:13.570
Let me make it simple for you.

644
00:35:13.737 --> 00:35:15.030
This right here?

645
00:35:15.197 --> 00:35:18.450
This blows up your career.
Poof. gone.

646
00:35:19.243 --> 00:35:20.619
But this...

647
00:35:22.204 --> 00:35:25.040
This keeps you safe.

648
00:35:25.791 --> 00:35:28.126
And it makes you mayor.

649
00:35:36.844 --> 00:35:38.262
Good decision.

650
00:35:41.807 --> 00:35:43.517
Now you work for me.

651
00:35:44.893 --> 00:35:47.980
First thing I need you to do.
pull your people off of Claudia.

652
00:35:49.398 --> 00:35:50.482
No.

653
00:35:51.567 --> 00:35:53.861
There's no way I can do that
without raising suspicion.

654
00:35:55.571 --> 00:35:57.739
Then pull 'em off
her girlfriend.

655
00:36:03.829 --> 00:36:05.414
I'll talk to you soon.

656
00:36:43.452 --> 00:36:45.329
Appreciate
this last-minute meet. Che.

657
00:36:46.413 --> 00:36:47.539
We got a new territory.

658
00:36:47.706 --> 00:36:48.790
-so I wanted to talk to you--

659
00:36:52.085 --> 00:36:53.587
Who the fuck is this?

660
00:36:54.922 --> 00:36:57.049
See. when I get into business
with people...

661
00:36:57.841 --> 00:36:59.635
I like to deal
with the same faces.

662
00:37:00.302 --> 00:37:02.387
Inconsistencies
are like a cancer.

663
00:37:03.180 --> 00:37:04.681
So where's your partner.
Sampson?

664
00:37:04.848 --> 00:37:06.224
Somethin' I should know?

665
00:37:07.517 --> 00:37:08.644
No. it's all good.

666
00:37:08.810 --> 00:37:10.938
Tommy just got some other shit
goin' on right now.

667
00:37:11.104 --> 00:37:13.231
Che. that's my brother. Jenard.

668
00:37:13.357 --> 00:37:15.859
Now. he ran CBI
while I was on the inside.

669
00:37:16.026 --> 00:37:19.446
So you can just consider him
a... an extension of me.

670
00:37:19.571 --> 00:37:20.656
My blood.

671
00:37:20.822 --> 00:37:22.658
I mean. hell. Che. he wouldn't--
he wouldn't be here

672
00:37:22.824 --> 00:37:24.326
unless I trusted him.

673
00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:34.628
I'm hearing you moved
on another gang.

674
00:37:35.462 --> 00:37:37.172
Yeah. The Yardies.

675
00:37:37.297 --> 00:37:40.217
How many times I have to
tell you not to start a war?

676
00:37:40.384 --> 00:37:41.927
And I understand that. Che.

677
00:37:42.094 --> 00:37:44.012
But it was relatively bloodless.

678
00:37:44.179 --> 00:37:46.598
And- and we ain't get
no pushback from nobody.

679
00:37:47.349 --> 00:37:49.810
A'ight? No war in the streets.
The shit's been handled.

680
00:37:50.602 --> 00:37:53.522
So we came here
to ask for more product.

681
00:37:54.773 --> 00:37:56.984
'Cause. Che. we ain't gon'
cost you money.

682
00:37:58.235 --> 00:37:59.695
We gon' make you
more of it.

683
00:37:59.861 --> 00:38:00.988
That's right.

684
00:38:04.241 --> 00:38:05.993
You shoulda led with that.

685
00:38:15.627 --> 00:38:17.421
- Yo.

686
00:38:18.338 --> 00:38:20.507
-What's goin' on?
-We got a package.

687
00:38:20.674 --> 00:38:22.134
From Kate.

688
00:38:22.300 --> 00:38:23.051
What is it?

689
00:38:23.218 --> 00:38:24.428
I don't know. I didn't open it.

690
00:38:24.553 --> 00:38:26.847
Why not? It ain't a bomb.

691
00:38:27.014 --> 00:38:29.016
Well. it's addressed
to both of us.

692
00:38:29.141 --> 00:38:31.226
You're too fuckin' polite.

693
00:38:43.030 --> 00:38:44.740
"You two are brothers...

694
00:38:45.407 --> 00:38:47.617
despite your differences."

695
00:38:47.784 --> 00:38:48.744
"Don't fuck that up."

696
00:38:48.910 --> 00:38:50.203
-"Kate."

697
00:38:51.079 --> 00:38:52.956
The woman's always had
a way with words.

698
00:39:00.505 --> 00:39:02.382
I think I know
what she's trying to say.

699
00:39:03.592 --> 00:39:05.177
You smarter than me. then.

700
00:39:09.598 --> 00:39:11.349
You know. this shit's
not that bad. actually.

701
00:39:11.516 --> 00:39:12.559
I mean. she do realize that

702
00:39:12.726 --> 00:39:14.061
she's the one that gave up
drinking. right?

703
00:39:14.227 --> 00:39:15.562
-Not us.
-Tommy...

704
00:39:16.271 --> 00:39:17.481
-About earlier--
-Oh. no. no. no.

705
00:39:17.647 --> 00:39:19.316
-Forget about it.
-No.

706
00:39:19.858 --> 00:39:20.942
No.

707
00:39:23.111 --> 00:39:24.362
You were right.

708
00:39:25.072 --> 00:39:27.824
Darnell... D-Mac...

709
00:39:28.575 --> 00:39:30.327
he's gonna do
what he's gonna do.

710
00:39:31.453 --> 00:39:34.081
And I can't control that.

711
00:39:35.415 --> 00:39:38.460
But if he's going to do it.
he's safer doing it with you.

712
00:39:40.212 --> 00:39:41.254
Thanks. JP.

713
00:39:41.838 --> 00:39:44.591
I'ma keep an eye on him.
I promise.

714
00:39:47.552 --> 00:39:50.472
You. uh... you think Kate
can stay sober this time?

715
00:39:50.639 --> 00:39:54.392
I think Kate trying to rescue
the last bit of wine

716
00:39:54.559 --> 00:39:56.228
at the bottom of a box
right now.

717
00:39:56.353 --> 00:39:58.939
Nah. I mean. I don't know. man.
She ain't never done it before.

718
00:39:59.106 --> 00:40:00.816
Not long term. anyway.

719
00:40:01.691 --> 00:40:02.609
One time...

720
00:40:03.193 --> 00:40:05.278
she did it for. like. maybe...

721
00:40:06.029 --> 00:40:08.156
if I'm not exaggerating.
two weeks.

722
00:40:08.323 --> 00:40:09.366
I was...

723
00:40:09.950 --> 00:40:11.284
eight or nine.

724
00:40:11.451 --> 00:40:13.078
Right before Ghost
moved in with us.

725
00:40:13.829 --> 00:40:16.164
I came home from school.
I opened the door.

726
00:40:16.289 --> 00:40:19.209
and I hear. "Tommy!
Close the door!"

727
00:40:20.001 --> 00:40:21.878
I'm like. "Why?"
She said...

728
00:40:22.671 --> 00:40:24.464
"I got seven pigeons."

729
00:40:25.257 --> 00:40:26.591
Yeah. she was gonna adopt them.

730
00:40:26.758 --> 00:40:28.093
-What?
- Yeah.

731
00:40:28.260 --> 00:40:29.344
-Why?
- I don't know.

732
00:40:29.469 --> 00:40:30.804
I guess she just
needed something

733
00:40:30.929 --> 00:40:32.139
to keep her mind occupied.

734
00:40:32.305 --> 00:40:33.473
Well. what happened?

735
00:40:33.640 --> 00:40:34.891
-To what. the pigeons?
- Yeah.

736
00:40:35.058 --> 00:40:37.352
They died.
She forgot to feed 'em.

737
00:40:39.354 --> 00:40:40.605
That's fuckin' Kate.

738
00:40:41.273 --> 00:40:43.024
Well. maybe this time'll
be different.

739
00:40:44.734 --> 00:40:46.987
To Kate staying sober.

740
00:40:47.737 --> 00:40:49.489
Promise me you won't
keep your hopes up.

741
00:40:52.742 --> 00:40:53.869
To Kate.

742
00:41:01.918 --> 00:41:03.670
So what's our next move?

743
00:41:04.212 --> 00:41:05.630
You meet with him again.

744
00:41:05.797 --> 00:41:08.383
How is that a good plan?

745
00:41:09.050 --> 00:41:11.219
If I meet with him again.
I have to go alone.

746
00:41:11.386 --> 00:41:13.013
Why the fuck would I do that?

747
00:41:13.180 --> 00:41:14.306
Because...

748
00:41:15.223 --> 00:41:17.559
I wouldn't object
if Tommy was the one

749
00:41:17.726 --> 00:41:19.561
who didn't walk away
from the meeting.

750
00:41:20.687 --> 00:41:22.522
Are you saying what I think
you're saying?

751
00:41:22.647 --> 00:41:24.107
I'm saying...

752
00:41:24.608 --> 00:41:26.276
Tommy fucking Egan

753
00:41:26.443 --> 00:41:29.279
is a noxious.
toxic piece of garbage.

754
00:41:30.238 --> 00:41:33.325
And no one is gonna cry
crocodile tears over his grave.

755
00:41:34.409 --> 00:41:36.745
And why should I trust
that this isn't a setup?

756
00:41:36.912 --> 00:41:39.623
Because...
there's a deal attached.

757
00:41:40.999 --> 00:41:42.334
If Tommy is...

758
00:41:43.210 --> 00:41:44.544
taken out of the equation.

759
00:41:44.711 --> 00:41:46.004
I'll let you into the gap.

760
00:41:46.880 --> 00:41:48.340
All you have to do
is serve me up

761
00:41:48.465 --> 00:41:50.175
the occasional piece
of red meat.

762
00:41:50.342 --> 00:41:51.843
and. as mayor...

763
00:41:52.969 --> 00:41:55.096
I'll arrange it
so you can operate unimpeded

764
00:41:55.222 --> 00:41:56.181
here in Chicago.

765
00:41:59.392 --> 00:42:01.519
What about testifying
against Ortega?

766
00:42:01.686 --> 00:42:03.521
